      <Desc>Bellevue Discovery Preschool - beginning Sept 2012 we offered our program to 24- 3, 4 &amp; 5 year olds to help them develop to their highest potential intellectually, socially, emotionally &amp; physically. As of June 30th 2018 we had a full enrollment of 24 children in the preschool program. Our preschool program is recommended by local independent gifted schools, IQ testers and pediatricians for young children whose cognitive abilities are outside the norm. We offer a part-time preschool program, a weekly newsletter, parent-teacher conferences, field trips and an active alumni parent community. We had 100 visitors at admissions events this year, representing approximately 55 separate families.</Desc>
      <ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp>
        <Desc>Parent Coaching - is a service we offer to our enrolled and alumni families. We had 46 separate Parent Coaching sessions for the 2018-2019 year. These sessions help our families with topics such as educational consulting, child development, parenting, gifted education, schooling needs and planning for future schooling needs. Our staff communicated with families over the phone, in person, through email, and in small monthly discussion groups.</Desc>
      </ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp>
      <ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp>
        <Desc>Parent Education - is a free community service open to the public. Our mission is to raise awareness of the unique needs of young gifted children. We had 42 families in our community attend 4 Parent Education Seminars and events this year. Seminar topics included Educational Philosophies, Children's Temperaments, Gifted Programs, Independent School Admissions, and Young Gifted Children.</Desc>
      </ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp>
